
[1]negboor

   NEGBOOR, n.

   1. One who lives near another. In large towns, a neighbor is one who
   lives within a few doors. In the country, a neighbor may live at a
   greater distance; a dn in new settlements, where the people are thinly
   scattered over the country, a neighbor may be distant several miles.
   Such is the use of the word in the United States.

   2. One who lives in familiarity with another; a word of civility.

   3. An intimate; a confidant.

   4. A fellow being. Acts 7.

   5. One of the human race; any one that needs our help, or to whom we
   have an opportunity of doing good.

   6. A country that is near.
